text: Biasmia antennalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Hunt and Breuning in 1957. It is known from South Africa and Zimbabwe.BioLib.cz - Biasmia antennalis. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Crossotini Category:Beetles described in 1957
title: Biasmia antennalis
